**Page Title:** COM - Briefs Community - SAINTCON

**Overview:**
- **Community Purpose:** The community focuses on various security topics and provides a platform for short talks called "Briefs," which are 10 minutes or less. Participants can share experiences from successful or failed projects and the lessons learned.
  
**Key Features:**
- **Presentations:** Participants are encouraged to present on topics of interest. A small slideshow is suggested as visual support.
- **Sign-up for Presentations:** Interested individuals can sign up to present via a provided link.
- **Community Engagement:** Attendees benefit from learning diverse topics, while presenters improve their public speaking skills.

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Monday:** Closed
- **Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday:** During Lunch
- **Friday:** No Briefs

**Special Offerings:**
- MiniBadge for participants, with specific designs available.
- Desktop wallpaper from the community is available for download.

**Links:**
- [Sign Up Here](https://forms.gle/76Ex5bDKfhoic4RE9): For presenting a "Brief."
- [Download Wallpaper](https://saintcon.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Briefs-2023_5K_Wallpaper.png).

**Contact and Support:**
- For assistance, community members can reach out for specific support ranging from attendee questions to sponsor inquiries.

**Social Media Links:**
